function countLargestGroup(n) {
    let freq = new Array(37).fill(0);
    let maxGroupSize = 0, maxGroupCount = 0;

    for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        let sum = 0, num = i;
        while (num !== 0) {
            sum += num % 10;
            num = Math.floor(num / 10);
        }
        freq[sum]++;
        maxGroupSize = Math.max(maxGroupSize, freq[sum]);
    }

    for (let i = 0; i < 37; i++) {
        if (freq[i] === maxGroupSize) {
            maxGroupCount++;
        }
    }

    return maxGroupCount;
}
```


    We create an array `freq` to store the frequency of the sizes of the groups. Iterate through numbers 1 to `n` and calculate the sum of the digits of each number. Use this sum as an index to increment the frequency count in the array. At each step, we also update the maximum group size.

After that, we iterate through the frequency array and count the number of groups that have the maximum group size.

Finally, return the count of the largest groups.

